I"m<h2 id="git-installation">Git installation</h2>

<p>The next post focuses on using git in a docs as code environment. Pr</p>

<p>For MacOS, you will need <a href="https://developer.apple.com/xcode/resources/">Xcode and Command Line Tools</a> as well as Git. To check if you have Command Line Tool installed, run:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>$ xcode-select -v
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>If you see a version number, you are good to go. Otherwise, follow the instructions for installing in the link above.</p>

